<!-- ==========================================================

Description:
User login page template.

This view provides the interface for user authentication,
including email/password login and Google OAuth sign-in.

Responsibilities:
- Render login form inputs.
- Provide authentication triggers.
- Offer navigation to password recovery and registration.
- Support internationalization for dynamic text.

Structure:
- Includes global header and footer partials.
- Organized using BEM naming convention.
- Divided into:
  1. Login form section
  2. Alternative authentication options

Client-Side Behavior:
- Form submission triggers authentication logic (login.js).
- Google button initiates OAuth flow (google.js).
- Authentication state handled via auth.js and authState.js.
- UI updates dynamically based on authentication result.

Dependencies:
- login.js
- google.js
- auth.js
- authState.js
- firebase.js
- i18n system
- Global bundle.min.js

Security Notes:
- Password field uses type="password" for secure input.
- Authentication logic is handled client-side via Firebase.
- No sensitive credentials are processed directly in this template.
- Form uses required validation attributes.

========================================================== -->

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="login">
  <h1 class="login__titulo" data-i18n="logintitulo"></h1>

  <form id="login-form" class="login__form">
    <label class="login__form--tituloEmail" data-i18n="emailLogin"></label>
    <input id="login-email" class="login__form--input" type="email" required />

    <label class="login__form--passw" data-i18n="passwordLogin"></label>
    <input id="login-pass" class="login__form--input" type="password" required />

    <button class="login__form--submit" type="submit" data-i18n="submitLogin"></button>
  </form>

  <div class="login__options">
    <button id="google-btn" class="login__options--google" data-i18n="google"></button>
    <a id="forgot-btn" class="login__options--olvidar" href="/olvidar" data-i18n="forgotPassowrd"></a>
    <a class="login__options--crearCuenta" href="/register" data-i18n="createAcc"></a>
  </div>

</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>